com.github.javaparser.ast.expr

Class LambdaExpr

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.javaparser.ast.Node
      • com.github.javaparser.ast.expr.Expression
        • com.github.javaparser.ast.expr.LambdaExpr
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    NodeWithParameters<LambdaExpr>, NodeWithRange<Node>, NodeWithTokenRange<Node>, Observable, Visitable, HasParentNode<Node>, Cloneable

    public final class LambdaExpr
extends Expression
implements NodeWithParameters<LambdaExpr>

    A lambda expression

    Java 1-7

    Does not exist.

    Java 8+

    (a, b) -> a + b
    a -> ...
    (Long a) -> { println(a); }

    The parameters are on the left side of the ->. If a parameter uses type inference (it has no type specified) then its type is set to UnknownType. If they are in ( ), "isEnclosingParameters" is true.
    The body is to the right of the ->. The body is either a BlockStatement when it is in { } braces, or an ExpressionStatement when it is not in braces.

    Author:
    Raquel Pau
